Write a python program which takes user input and do the following tasks:
a) print number of vowels in the entered string
b) print the length of the entered string
c) convert string element to uppercase, lowercase, capitalise the first letter, title-case
and swapcase
d) print the letters which are at odd index
s=input("enter a string:")
print("number of vowels in entered string:")
for i in s:
div    if (i=='a' or i=='e' or i=='o' or i=='u'):
        print(i)
    else:
        print("no vowels in the string")

    length_of_string=len(s)
    print("length of entered string is:",length_of_string)

    upperCase=s.upper()
    lowerCase=s.lower()
    firstCapital=s.capitalize()
    swapCase=s.swapcase()
    print("string in uppercase is:",uppercase)
    print("string in lowercase is:",lowercase)
    print("string with first letter capital is:",firstcapital)
    print("string in swap case is:",swapcase)

    print("letters at odd index are:")
    for i in range(0,length_of_string):
        print(s[i])
